<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Batybot OAuth Setup</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            max-width: 800px;
            margin: 50px auto;
            padding: 20px;
            background: #0f0f23;
            color: #cccccc;
        }
        .container {
            background: #1a1a2e;
            padding: 30px;
            border-radius: 8px;
            border: 1px solid #333;
        }
        h1 {
            color: #9146ff;
            text-align: center;
        }
        .auth-btn {
            display: inline-block;
            background: #9146ff;
            color: white;
            padding: 12px 24px;
            text-decoration: none;
            border-radius: 4px;
            font-weight: bold;
            text-align: center;
            margin: 20px auto;
            display: block;
            width: 200px;
        }
        .auth-btn:hover {
            background: #772ce8;
        }
        .info {
            background: #2a2a3e;
            padding: 15px;
            border-radius: 4px;
            margin: 20px 0;
            border-left: 4px solid #9146ff;
        }
        code {
            background: #2a2a3e;
            padding: 2px 6px;
            border-radius: 3px;
            font-family: monospace;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>ðŸ¦‡ Batybot OAuth Setup</h1>

        <div class="info">
            <h3>Welcome to Batybot Setup!</h3>
            <p>To get started, you need to authorize Batybot to access your Twitch account. This will allow the bot to:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Read and send chat messages</li>
                <li>Read and send whispers</li>
            </ul>
            <p><strong>Note:</strong> Make sure you have set the following environment variables:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><code>TWITCH_CLIENT_ID</code> - Your Twitch application client ID</li>
                <li><code>TWITCH_CLIENT_SECRET</code> - Your Twitch application client secret</li>
                <li><code>TWITCH_USER</code> - The username the bot will use</li>
                <li><code>TWITCH_CHANNEL</code> - The channel the bot will join</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <a href="{{.AuthURL}}" class="auth-btn">ðŸ”— Authorize with Twitch</a>

        <div class="info">
            <p><strong>What happens next?</strong></p>
            <ol>
                <li>Click the authorize button above</li>
                <li>Log in to Twitch and authorize the application</li>
                <li>You'll be redirected back here with your tokens</li>
                <li>The bot will automatically start and connect to chat!</li>
            </ol>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>

